# Bulls & Cows — Improvement Plan

Use this plan when adding features or refactoring. Prioritize small, shippable slices.

## Current State

- **Stack**: Expo SDK 55, React Native, TypeScript
- **Game model**: 9 innings, 3 outs per inning, 3-digit unique secret, baseball-themed scoring
- **Core logic**: `src/lib/game.ts`, state in `src/hooks/useGame.ts`
- **UI**: Monolithic `App.tsx` (~900 lines, inline components + styles)
- **Docs drift**: `README.md` still describes a 10-attempt limit (outdated)

---

## Phase 1 — Quick Wins (Logic + UX)

### Logic

- [ ] **Disable Enter until guess is complete** — `submitGuess` already validates; disable the Enter key and show helper text when `currentGuess.length < DIGIT_COUNT`.
- [ ] **Gray out used digits on keypad** — pass `currentGuess` into keypad; dim keys whose digit is already entered (duplicate prevention is silent today).
- [ ] **Block input during sound/modal transitions** — `inningEndVisible` / `gameEndVisible` already gate input; also disable keypad while `playCallSequence` is in flight to avoid double-submit.
- [ ] **Sync README with actual rules** — document innings, outs, and run scoring; remove the 10-attempt limit.

### UI

- [ ] **Per-digit feedback in attempt history** — color each digit in `AttemptRow`: green = strike, yellow = ball, gray = out (reuse strike-position logic from guess boxes).
- [ ] **Shake or pulse on invalid submit** — brief animation on guess boxes when validation fails (replace or supplement `Alert`).
- [ ] **Perfect-game celebration** — when `inningResults.filter(r => r.scored).length === TOTAL_INNINGS`, show distinct copy/emoji on game-end modal.
- [ ] **Settings toggles** — sound on/off, haptics on/off (persist with `AsyncStorage`).

---

## Phase 2 — Structure & Reliability

### Logic

- [ ] **Unit tests for `game.ts`** — cover `scoreGuess`, `isValidGuessDigits`, `generateSecretDigits` (uniqueness, range, edge cases like all-outs guess).
- [ ] **Extract pure inning reducer** — move inning transitions (`submitGuess` outcome → next state) into testable functions in `src/lib/game.ts` or `src/lib/inning.ts`.
- [ ] **High-score / stats persistence** — best run total, perfect games count, average attempts per scored inning.
- [ ] **Undo last guess (optional)** — allow one undo per inning before next submit; clears last attempt and recalculates outs.

### UI / Architecture

- [ ] **Split `App.tsx`** into:
  - `src/screens/HomeScreen.tsx`
  - `src/screens/GameScreen.tsx`
  - `src/components/` — `Pill`, `Keypad`, `GuessBoxes`, `AttemptRow`, `InningScoreboard`, `GameModal`
  - `src/theme/` — shared colors, spacing, typography (replace magic hex values)
- [ ] **Remove dead code** — unused `playOneShot` in `useSound.ts`, unused styles (`hero`, `howtoContent`, `secretHintArea`, etc.).

---

## Phase 3 — Polish & Accessibility

### Logic

- [ ] **Configurable difficulty** — optional 4-digit mode or fewer innings (constants in `src/constants/game.ts`).
- [ ] **Daily challenge** — seeded secret from date string so all players share the same puzzle.
- [ ] **Hint system** — after N failed attempts in an inning, reveal one digit position (limit hints per inning).

### UI

- [ ] **Animations** — `LayoutAnimation` or Reanimated for attempt list insert, out-dot fill, modal enter.
- [ ] **Accessibility** — `accessibilityLabel` on keypad and guess boxes; announce S/B/O results via `AccessibilityInfo.announceForAccessibility`.
- [ ] **Dark mode** — theme tokens + `useColorScheme`; StatusBar follows scheme.
- [ ] **Responsive layout** — constrain max width on tablets; optional landscape scoreboard sidebar.
- [ ] **Onboarding** — first-launch tooltip or collapsible “How to play” on game screen.

---

## Implementation Notes

### Scoring logic (do not change without tests)

```typescript
// strikes: digit match at index
// balls: digit in secret, wrong index
// outs: DIGIT_COUNT - strikes - balls
```

### File ownership

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Pure game rules | `src/lib/game.ts` |
| Session / inning state | `src/hooks/useGame.ts` |
| Audio | `src/hooks/useSound.ts` |
| Screens & components | `src/screens/`, `src/components/` |
| Tunables | `src/constants/game.ts` |

### Conventions

- Keep baseball metaphor in copy (innings, runs, outs, strikes, balls).
- Prefer haptics + inline feedback over blocking `Alert` dialogs for validation.
- Match existing visual language: rounded cards, pill badges, blue primary / green success / red outs.
- Minimize scope per PR — one phase item or a small cluster (e.g. keypad disable + used-digit styling).

---

## Suggested Next Task

Start with **Phase 1**: disable Enter when incomplete, gray used keypad digits, per-digit attempt coloring, and README sync. These improve feel without architectural churn.
